WEBVTT

00:02.837 --> 00:04.919
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes.

00:05.548 --> 00:07.129
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

00:10.553 --> 00:14.091
Sword not there.
Original owned by
man named Linderman.

00:14.265 --> 00:17.348
He's a client of mine.
Get your car.
You're going back to Vegas.

00:18.269 --> 00:21.602
You're going home.
The charges against you have
been dropped, Miss Sanders.

00:21.772 --> 00:23.808
And as far as Linderman
is concerned?

00:24.025 --> 00:26.311
Don't worry about
tomorrow's problems today.

00:26.611 --> 00:29.694
Officer Parkman,
we're enforcing a
six-month suspension.

00:29.822 --> 00:31.528
We're gonna need your gun
and your badge.

00:31.616 --> 00:33.857
Nothing in my life
has been real.

00:33.951 --> 00:36.158
My dad obviously doesn't work
in a paper factory.

00:37.580 --> 00:39.571
He's gone now.
You're okay.

00:39.790 --> 00:42.372
MR. BENNET: This is my friend.
He's gonna make
everything okay.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.461
Mom?
Claire?

00:45.421 --> 00:47.628
l was hoping you could
tell me about my father.

00:47.715 --> 00:50.832
Now, that's complicated.
He's kind of a big shot.

00:53.387 --> 00:54.843
(PHONE RINGING)

00:56.807 --> 00:57.967
Hello?

01:00.019 --> 01:01.429
MEREDITH: You might not
remember me.

01:01.520 --> 01:05.058
We haven’t spoken
in a long time,
but ljust had...

01:06.984 --> 01:09.145
Our daughter just found me.

01:11.155 --> 01:13.441
Did you hear
what ljust said?

01:14.867 --> 01:16.368
She’s alive.

01:19.914 --> 01:21.154
Meredith?

01:24.001 --> 01:25.662
We need to talk.

01:28.089 --> 01:30.205
Nathan,
are you still there?

01:30.716 --> 01:32.547
It's been 14 years.

01:34.345 --> 01:35.755
I went to your funeral.

01:35.846 --> 01:38.132
Look, that fire,
it wasn't an accident.

01:38.224 --> 01:39.464
Someone was out
to get me,

01:39.558 --> 01:44.018
and the police, theyjust
assumed I was dead,
so I ran.

01:45.898 --> 01:47.058
And our daughter?

01:47.149 --> 01:50.016
Well, she’s got an angel
on her shoulder, that one.

01:50.111 --> 01:53.569
She was adopted by
a nice family here in Texas.

01:53.948 --> 01:57.111
She's 16 now.
She's beautiful.

01:58.035 --> 02:00.026
She's got blonde hair
like me,

02:00.121 --> 02:02.658
and she is smart
just like you.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.533
Maybe one day she'll
run for Congress.

02:08.462 --> 02:12.831
The timing of your call
two weeks before my election,

02:12.925 --> 02:14.711
that's not a coincidence,
is it?

02:15.970 --> 02:19.212
A child born out of wedlock,
that's big news. You wouldn't
want that to come out.

02:20.099 --> 02:21.805
Ruin things for you.

02:24.228 --> 02:26.059
How much do you want?

02:27.898 --> 02:29.149
Oh...

02:29.233 --> 02:30.939
A hundred thousand?

02:34.155 --> 02:35.315
Yeah.

02:37.033 --> 02:38.898
That ought to cover it.

02:39.910 --> 02:41.992
I’ll let you know
where to send it.

02:50.504 --> 02:52.040
Nice and easy.

02:54.633 --> 02:56.089
Mom, are you okay?

02:56.719 --> 02:57.834
I've been better.

02:57.928 --> 02:59.509
Oh, she'll be fine.

02:59.597 --> 03:02.509
She needs a little rest,
little time to recover.

03:02.975 --> 03:04.556
Recover from what?

03:04.643 --> 03:08.636
She had an appointment
with a neurologist,
who ran some tests.

03:08.773 --> 03:09.933
What kind of tests?

03:10.024 --> 03:12.310
Your mother's been
having some headaches.

03:13.944 --> 03:17.357
Yeah, she's also been
having some memory loss.
Did you tell them that?

03:17.865 --> 03:19.526
Of course, Claire.

03:22.578 --> 03:24.239
l'm handling it.

03:36.967 --> 03:38.503
(DOOR CLOSES)

03:39.678 --> 03:42.055
Don't worry, honey.
I'll be fine.

03:42.473 --> 03:44.805
Mr. Muggles
isn't worried, is he?

03:45.518 --> 03:47.008
No, he's not.

04:01.784 --> 04:03.365
NlKl: D.L. won't be fooled.

04:03.452 --> 04:04.828
Sure, he will.

04:04.912 --> 04:07.824
Love is blind,
and if last night
is any indication

04:07.915 --> 04:10.998
he won't be able
to see anything
for a long time.

04:13.379 --> 04:15.335
D.L.: Nik, baby,
I've got to get going.

04:15.423 --> 04:16.788
I'll be right there.

04:18.509 --> 04:19.498
(WHISTLES)

04:20.678 --> 04:23.090
Don't you look
all secret service.

04:23.180 --> 04:25.592
Is this standard issue
for bodyguards?

04:25.683 --> 04:27.594
Bodyguards?
We're not called
bodyguards anymore, honey,

04:27.685 --> 04:29.016
it's private security.

04:29.270 --> 04:31.886
Whatever you want to call it,
it's paying the bills.

04:32.690 --> 04:34.396
MICAH: Are we ever
gonna talk about it?

04:34.483 --> 04:36.019
Talk about what?

04:36.110 --> 04:38.772
What we can do.
Our powers.

04:40.364 --> 04:42.855
ljust feel like
we're supposed to be
fighting crime or something.

04:43.451 --> 04:47.444
That's true. But for now,
can you just have fun
at school, my young genius?

04:48.247 --> 04:49.236
Yep.

04:52.877 --> 04:55.789
All right, baby,
there's a package for you
over on the table.

04:55.880 --> 04:57.245
Thanks.

04:57.715 --> 04:58.704
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:08.809 --> 05:10.140
Are you taking your gun?

05:10.227 --> 05:14.561
It's the difference
between 500 and 350 a day,
my carry permit.

05:15.065 --> 05:16.680
You're not gonna need it,
though, right?

05:17.443 --> 05:20.276
(SIGHS) I'm basically
a glorified babysitter.

05:20.362 --> 05:21.693
Nothing's gonna happen.

05:21.780 --> 05:22.860
I hope not.

05:24.074 --> 05:27.157
Thank God you called.
Playing house
was making me cranky.

05:29.246 --> 05:32.488
I understand.
Guy stole his money.
He wants him dead.

05:32.583 --> 05:35.074
(CHUCKLES)
What Mr. Linderman wants,
Mr. Linderman gets.

05:37.338 --> 05:40.922
WOMAN ON PA: The white curb
is for immediate loading and
unloading of passengers only.

05:41.008 --> 05:42.418
No parking.

05:42.927 --> 05:44.258
l'm Malsky.

05:45.137 --> 05:47.128
Matt Parkman,
here to protect you, sir.

05:52.937 --> 05:53.926
Bang.

06:13.374 --> 06:15.285
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

06:23.509 --> 06:25.090
(HIRO SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

07:01.338 --> 07:02.669
