07:03.090 --> 07:04.591
Are you okay, miss?

07:08.012 --> 07:09.673
Anything we can do
to help?

07:10.222 --> 07:11.758
No, I couldn't possibly,

07:11.849 --> 07:14.431
I mean,
we're complete strangers.

07:18.188 --> 07:20.395
l'm Ando.
This is my friend Hiro.

07:21.609 --> 07:24.021
Hi. I'm Hope.

07:29.700 --> 07:32.533
So, where we headed?

07:33.203 --> 07:35.364
Diamond District,
Broadway and Sixth.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.743
What a beautiful day
to be in Los Angeles.

07:38.834 --> 07:40.449
Look at this weather.
And the air...

07:40.544 --> 07:41.784
What's your name again?

07:41.879 --> 07:43.619
Parkman, Matt Parkman.

07:43.714 --> 07:46.171
Listen, Parkman,
the job is simple.

07:46.258 --> 07:49.295
You drive me downtown.
We meet a man.
I make a deal.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.172
Then you drive me
back to the airport.

07:51.263 --> 07:53.879
You just make sure
no one bothers me.

07:54.391 --> 07:55.927
That includes you.

07:58.812 --> 08:01.849
MALSK Y: Hope this loser
knows how to use his gun.

08:01.940 --> 08:03.555
Otherwise we’re both dead.

08:10.199 --> 08:11.655
My name's Dr. Mohinder Suresh.

08:11.742 --> 08:13.448
It's very important
that I speak with him.

08:13.535 --> 08:14.524
(PHONE DISCONNECTS)

08:14.912 --> 08:16.994
I assure you
my interest is legitimate.

08:17.081 --> 08:19.242
My name is
Dr. Mohinder Suresh.

08:20.918 --> 08:22.829
It's really rather complicated
to explain over the phone.

08:22.920 --> 08:23.909
This is
Dr. Mohinder Suresh.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.744
There's a certain
genetic trait.

08:26.924 --> 08:28.880
Have you noticed anything
unusual about his behavior?

08:28.967 --> 08:30.252
My name is
Dr. Mohinder Suresh.

08:30.344 --> 08:31.333
You still there?

08:35.933 --> 08:38.174
ANSWERING MACH/NE:
One new message.

08:38.268 --> 08:40.930
ZANE.‘ Hi, this is Zane,

08:42.106 --> 08:45.064
Zane Taylor. Z-A-N-E Taylor.

08:46.527 --> 08:49.064
/ got your phone message,

08:50.280 --> 08:53.693
and something’s
happening to me.
I can’t control it. I...

08:54.368 --> 08:56.029
/ think we need to talk.
Please hurry.

08:56.120 --> 08:59.112
Can you come see me
right away? It’s really...

09:03.293 --> 09:05.375
MAN: Five minutes, ladies.
Five minutes.

09:05.462 --> 09:07.544
HOPE: We've dated
for a few months.

09:07.631 --> 09:09.622
He lives in LA.
Comes to visit.

09:09.717 --> 09:12.003
And, at first,
he was really sweet.

09:12.136 --> 09:14.468
But now he's just horrible.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.545
He even hit me once.

09:20.310 --> 09:22.050
Your boyfriend
did this to you?

09:22.146 --> 09:23.431
I'm sorry.

09:24.732 --> 09:26.723
I left this morning
while he was sleeping,

09:26.817 --> 09:28.398
and then
I forgot my bag.

09:28.485 --> 09:30.567
lt's pink and it has
rhinestones on it,

09:30.654 --> 09:32.565
and it's got all my money
and my credit cards.

09:32.656 --> 09:34.897
It even has my
family photos in it.

09:34.992 --> 09:36.857
That I can't replace.

09:39.288 --> 09:41.404
I should go up there
and talk to him.

09:41.498 --> 09:43.329
Maybe he won't be so mad.

09:43.417 --> 09:45.954
No. We will do it.

09:46.170 --> 09:47.205
Eh?

09:49.923 --> 09:51.424
Excuse us, please.

09:58.432 --> 10:00.343
(SPEAKING IN JAPANESE)

10:24.249 --> 10:27.537
Hang on. Did you two say
something about Mr. Linderman?

10:27.628 --> 10:29.459
Yes. You know him?

10:29.546 --> 10:31.707
No, not personally,
but everybody knows who he is.

10:31.799 --> 10:33.209
I know people who do.

10:33.300 --> 10:34.506
That's great.

10:37.221 --> 10:40.054
If we get your bag,
can you introduce us?

10:40.891 --> 10:42.381
Yeah, I can do that.

10:43.060 --> 10:44.391
We still have a problem.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.059
How do we
get past security?

10:48.398 --> 10:49.774
l have an idea.

10:58.408 --> 10:59.488
GUSTAVSON: Who's there?

10:59.576 --> 11:00.827
AN DO: Room service.

11:04.122 --> 11:05.828
I didn't order room service.

11:06.875 --> 11:09.082
Complimentary,
for high roller.

11:14.299 --> 11:15.914
Ah, very nice room.

11:21.932 --> 11:23.593
How are you today?

11:33.652 --> 11:34.937
You're done.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.577
(SHOWER RUNNING)

12:07.519 --> 12:09.020
UNJAPANESE)

13:45.575 --> 13:49.409
ZANE: Oh, God, hurry.
Please hurry.

13:50.706 --> 13:52.412
Oh God, hurry.

13:53.750 --> 13:57.413
Hurry. Please hurry.
Please hurry.

13:57.921 --> 13:59.127
(DOORBELL RINGS)

14:06.680 --> 14:08.341
Dr. Suresh?

14:11.852 --> 14:12.932
Yes.

14:16.398 --> 14:17.478
Yes.

14:17.691 --> 14:19.773
Thank God. Come in.

14:24.448 --> 14:25.654
Come in.

14:31.371 --> 14:32.872
l was starting to think
you weren't gonna show.

14:32.956 --> 14:34.617
I didn't know
what I was gonna do.

14:35.208 --> 14:37.073
I mean, look at what
I'm living with.

14:37.169 --> 14:38.500
Yes, | see
what you mean.

14:38.587 --> 14:40.043
I'm just a regular guy.

14:40.130 --> 14:43.873
I mean, I've never
been different, or special.

14:43.967 --> 14:47.835
I mean, no one would
even look at me twice
walking down the street.

14:50.474 --> 14:52.385
lguess
I should show you.

14:52.476 --> 14:53.556
Right?

14:55.062 --> 14:57.644
What I do,
you need to see it, right?

14:58.440 --> 14:59.930
Yes, of course.

15:00.609 --> 15:04.147
I haven't left the apartment
for three weeks,

15:04.529 --> 15:06.269
I'm going a little crazy.

15:10.410 --> 15:12.321
Maybe you should step back.

15:12.621 --> 15:14.532
It can get a little messy.

15:20.504 --> 15:22.210
(SURGING)

15:22.964 --> 15:25.501
ANGELA: We reap
what we sow, Nathan.

15:25.842 --> 15:28.128
You have no one to blame
but yourself.

15:28.970 --> 15:30.710
I'll go down to Texas
and handle it.

15:30.806 --> 15:32.091
So close
to the election?

15:32.182 --> 15:33.922
Don't be ridiculous.

15:34.017 --> 15:35.302
If the press
gets wind of this,

15:35.393 --> 15:37.770
especially on the heels
of the Linderman scandal...

15:37.854 --> 15:40.015
I cared about
Meredith once.

15:41.024 --> 15:43.515
I owe her more
than a phone call.
I owe them both.

15:44.528 --> 15:47.486
Besides,
l'm this girl's father, Mom.

15:47.572 --> 15:49.312
You're a glorified
sperm donor.

15:49.407 --> 15:51.147
Don't get
emotionally attached.

15:53.453 --> 15:54.784
How can you be so cold?

15:54.871 --> 15:56.122
Because I know you, Nathan.

15:56.206 --> 15:58.993
Beneath the gruff exterior,
you're a sap.

15:59.334 --> 16:02.076
And the moment that young girl
looks at you with those sad,
little weepy eyes,

16:02.170 --> 16:04.161
you're lost,
you're finished.

16:04.256 --> 16:08.420
You'll start giving,
she'll start taking,
until there's nothing left.

16:08.510 --> 16:10.421
So prioritize, Nathan.

16:11.096 --> 16:13.052
Wire the money to Texas.

16:13.515 --> 16:16.097
Focus on the people
who really matter.

16:23.608 --> 16:24.893
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

16:28.905 --> 16:30.156
How's Mom?

16:30.240 --> 16:32.105
Your mother's resting.

16:33.410 --> 16:36.243
So I understand you and Zach
cut school yesterday.

16:36.329 --> 16:38.035
Mom said we could.

16:38.331 --> 16:40.196
It was for a report.

16:40.917 --> 16:42.908
We went to the aquarium.

16:43.295 --> 16:45.035
With these tickets?

16:45.589 --> 16:49.127
Printed from your computer?
These fake tickets, Claire?

16:49.593 --> 16:51.174
You're spying on me?

16:51.261 --> 16:53.923
I don't know where you were,
and I don't want to know.

16:54.014 --> 16:56.471
You're a teenager.
You need to assert
your independence,

16:56.558 --> 16:58.344
but this behavior

17:00.270 --> 17:01.885
is unacceptable.

17:01.980 --> 17:03.891
You're grounded,
young lady.

17:03.982 --> 17:07.816
You're to be home
everyday at 5:00 sharp,
until further notice.

17:08.153 --> 17:10.439
What? You can't do that!
You have no right!

17:10.530 --> 17:11.770
I'm your father!

17:11.865 --> 17:13.355
You're not my real father.

17:16.828 --> 17:18.864
No, I'm not.

17:18.955 --> 17:20.491
But I'm as close
as you've got.

17:20.582 --> 17:24.325
So you'll stay home at night
until you earn our trust back.

17:27.964 --> 17:28.953
(DOOR CLOSES)

17:29.257 --> 17:30.872
(PHONE RING/NG)

17:30.967 --> 17:32.377
MEREDITH: Hello?
Hi.

17:33.053 --> 17:34.213
It's me, Claire.

17:34.304 --> 17:37.137
Do you have
a second to talk
about my father?

17:37.224 --> 17:38.964
Oh, hey, Claire,
I'm glad you called.

17:39.059 --> 17:42.051
Talk about coincidence.
I found your father.

17:42.646 --> 17:43.635
(GASPS)

17:44.439 --> 17:45.770
You're kidding.
What did he say?

17:45.857 --> 17:49.896
Well, after he
got over the shock
that we were both alive,

17:49.986 --> 17:51.442
